From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000008 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Jun 2026 16:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] mfd: omap-usb-host: steelhead UHH_HOSTCONFIG to match vendor

On the Nexus Q the soldered SMSC LAN9500A USB-ethernet enumerates under the
vendor Android 3.0 kernel but, before this change, the EHCI controller never
latched the port-1 connect under mainline even though GPIOs, clock, reset, VBUS
and the USB3320 ULPI PHY state were all identical (verified live: OTG_CTRL=0x66
on both; PORTSC CCS=1 vendor vs CCS=0 mainline).

The one register that differed is UHH_HOSTCONFIG. Measured on hardware, mainline
leaves it at 0x1c (INCR4/8/16 burst-enables only) and then sets APP_START_CLK;
the vendor instead programs 0x11c — P1_CONNECT_STATUS (bit 8) set and
APP_START_CLK (bit 31) left clear. Match the vendor: set P1_CONNECT_STATUS so
the EHCI latches the port-1 connect, and leave APP_START_CLK clear so the UHH
does not auto clock-gate and drop the port when idle.

With this, eth0 enumerates (0424:9e00 -> smsc95xx) and passes bidirectional
traffic on hardware.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
--- a/drivers/mfd/omap-usb-host.c
+++ b/drivers/mfd/omap-usb-host.c
@@ -445,7 +445,16 @@
 	reg |= (OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_INCR4_BURST_EN
 			| OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_INCR8_BURST_EN
 			| OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_INCR16_BURST_EN);
-	reg |= OMAP4_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_APP_START_CLK;
+	/*
+	 * Steelhead: match the vendor's working UHH_HOSTCONFIG (= 0x11C). The
+	 * soldered SMSC LAN9500A only reports connect on EHCI when
+	 * P1_CONNECT_STATUS (bit 8) is set, and the vendor leaves APP_START_CLK
+	 * (bit 31) CLEAR so the UHH does not auto clock-gate and drop the port.
+	 * Mainline does the opposite (APP_START_CLK set, P1_CONNECT_STATUS at the
+	 * reset default), so the EHCI never latches the connect (PORTSC CCS=0).
+	 */
+	reg |= OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_P1_CONNECT_STATUS;
+	reg &= ~OMAP4_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_APP_START_CLK;
 	reg &= ~OMAP_UHH_HOSTCONFIG_INCRX_ALIGN_EN;
 
 	switch (omap->usbhs_rev) {
